Cell type homology

all.paths <- c("//allen/programs/celltypes/workgroups/rnaseqanalysis/shiny/facs_seq/mouse_V1_ALM_20170405/",
               "//allen/programs/celltypes/workgroups/hct/CT_clustering/mouse_cell_vs_nuc/shinydb/20170818_VISp_L5_nuc_1/",
               "//allen/programs/celltypes/workgroups/hct/CT_clustering/mouse_cell_vs_nuc/shinydb/20170818_VISp_L5_cell_1/",
               "//allen/programs/celltypes/workgroups/hct/CT_clustering/mouse_cell_vs_nuc/shinydb/20170818_VISp_L5_snap25_1/",
               "//allen/programs/celltypes/workgroups/hct/CT_clustering/mouse_cell_vs_nuc/shinydb/20170818_VISp_L5_nuc_exon_1/")
names(all.paths) <- c("Mouse_V1_ALM", "Mouse_L5_Nuc", "Mouse_L5_Cell", "Mouse_L5_Snap25", "Mouse_L5_Nuc_Ex")
paths <- all.paths[c("Mouse_L5_Cell", "Mouse_V1_ALM")]

dend <- list()
anno <- list()
anno.cl <- list()
prop.all <- list()
for (dat1 in names(paths)) {
  if (file.exists(paste0(paths[[dat1]], "dend.RData"))) {
    dend[[dat1]] <- readRDS(paste0(paths[[dat1]], "dend.RData"))
  }
  anno[[dat1]] <- as.data.frame(read_feather(paste0(paths[[dat1]], "anno.feather")))
  colnames(anno[[dat1]])[colnames(anno[[dat1]]) == "final_label"] <- "cluster_label"  # KLUDGE - Tasic
  anno[[dat1]]$cluster_label <- sub("_outlier", "", anno[[dat1]]$cluster_label)  # KLUDGE - fix MTG labels
  prop1 <- as.data.frame(t(read_feather(paste0(paths[[dat1]], "prop.feather"))))
  colnames(prop1) <- unique(anno[[dat1]]$cluster_label)
  rownames(prop1) <- toupper(rownames(prop1))
  if (grepl("Mouse_V1_ALM", dat1)) {
    keep.cl <- unlist(dendrapply(dend[[dat1]], function(x) if (is.leaf(x)) attr(x, "label")))
    keep.cl <- intersect(keep.cl, unique(anno[[dat1]]$cluster_label[! grepl("ALM", anno[[dat1]]$cluster_label)]))
    keep.cl <- intersect(keep.cl, unique(anno[[dat1]]$cluster_label[anno[[dat1]]$category_label %in% c("GABAergic", "Glutamatergic")]))
    anno.cl1 <- unique(anno[[dat1]][, c("cluster_label", "fine_label",
                                        "coarse_label", "category_label")])
    confusion.score <- tapply(anno[[dat1]]$confusion_label, anno[[dat1]]$cluster_label, median)
    anno.cl1$confusion_score <- confusion.score[match(anno.cl1$cluster_label, names(confusion.score))]
  } else if (grepl("Mouse_L5", dat1)) {
    keep.cl <- unique(anno[[dat1]][anno[[dat1]]$cluster_type_label %in% c("inh", "exc", "glia"), c("cluster_label")])
    anno.cl1 <- data.frame(cluster_label = unique(anno[[dat1]][, c("cluster_label")]))
  } else {
    # keep.cl <- unlist(dendrapply(dend[[dat1]], function(x) if (is.leaf(x)) attr(x, "label")))
    # keep.cl <- paste0("cl", c(15,20,23,24,27,31,35,39,51,6,64,9,1,11,12,13,14,2,30,36,4,48,5,54,60,7,8))
    keep.cl <- unique(anno[[dat1]][, c("cluster_label")])
    anno.cl1 <- data.frame(cluster_label = unique(anno[[dat1]][, c("cluster_label")]))
  }
  
  # Common annotation
  cl.size <- table(anno[[dat1]]$cluster_label)
  anno.cl1$size <- cl.size[match(names(cl.size), anno.cl1$cluster_label)]
  anno.cl[[dat1]] <- anno.cl1[match(keep.cl, anno.cl1$cluster_label), ]
  anno[[dat1]] <- droplevels(subset(anno[[dat1]], cluster_label %in% keep.cl))
  prop1.subset <- prop1[, match(keep.cl, colnames(prop1))]
  prop.all[[dat1]] <- prop1.subset
}
beta <- list()
tau <- list()
for (dat1 in names(paths)) {
  beta[[dat1]] <- apply(prop[[dat1]], 1, calc_beta)
  tau[[dat1]] <- apply(prop[[dat1]], 1, calc_tau)
}

Select genes that mark clusters in both data sets.

# Empirical trade-off between number of genes and cell type specificity
cnt1.max <- ncol(prop[[1]]) / 3; cnt2.max <- ncol(prop[[2]]) / 3
# cnt1.max <- 110; cnt2.max <- 110 # AIBS / JCVI
# cnt1.max <- 20; cnt2.max <- 30 # AIBS / Mouse
keep.genes <- which(cnt[[1]] < cnt1.max & cnt[[2]] < cnt2.max & 
                      cnt[[1]] > 0 & cnt[[2]] > 0 & 
                      (beta[[1]] > 0.3 | tau[[1]] > 0.9) & 
                      (beta[[2]] > 0.3 | tau[[2]] > 0.9))  # JCVI/AIBS

prop.subset <- list()
cnt.subset <- list()
score.subset <- list()
for (dat1 in names(paths)) {
  prop.subset[[dat1]] <- prop[[dat1]][keep.genes, ]  # grep("L5a", colnames(prop[[dat1]]))
  cnt.subset[[dat1]] <- cnt[[dat1]][keep.genes]
  score.subset[[dat1]] <- beta[[dat1]][keep.genes]
}

cl.pairs <- expand.grid(colnames(prop.subset[[1]]), colnames(prop.subset[[2]]))

cor.all <- NULL
cor.wt <- score.subset[[1]] * score.subset[[2]]
for (i in 1:nrow(cl.pairs)) {
  cl1 <- cl.pairs[i, 1]
  cl2 <- cl.pairs[i, 2]
  cor1 <- cov.wt(cbind(prop.subset[[1]][, cl1], prop.subset[[2]][, cl2]), wt = cor.wt,
                 center = TRUE, cor = TRUE)$cor[1, 2]  # Weighted cor
  cor.all <- c(cor.all, cor1)
}
names(cor.all) <- apply(cl.pairs, 1, function(x) paste(x, collapse = "~"))

Compare expression of marker genes between species

Correlate proportion of cells/nuclei in each cluster expressing marker genes with FPKM > 1.

cor.m <- matrix(0, ncol(prop.subset[[1]]), ncol(prop.subset[[2]]), 
                dimnames = list(colnames(prop.subset[[1]]),
                                colnames(prop.subset[[2]])))

counter <- 0
for (i in 1:nrow(cl.pairs)) {
  counter <- counter + 1
  cl1 <- cl.pairs[i, 1]
  cl2 <- cl.pairs[i, 2]
  cor.m[cl1, cl2] <- cor.all[counter]
}

Threshold correlation matrix to identify best matching cell types (light blue), reciprocal best matches (dark blue), and unique best matches (red).

row.max <- t(apply(cor.m, 1, function(x) ifelse(x == max(x), 1, 0)))
col.max <- apply(cor.m, 2, function(x) ifelse(x == max(x), 2, 0))

cor.m2 <- row.max + col.max
cl.match <- which(cor.m2 == 3)
for (i in cl.match) {
  row.val <- cor.m2[row(cor.m2)[i], ]
  col.val <- cor.m2[, col(cor.m2)[i]]
  if (sum(row.val) == 3 & sum(col.val) == 3) {
    cor.m2[i] <- 4
  }
}


# Scale plot by difference in correlation
cor.diff.row <- t(apply(cor.m, 1, function(x) x - max(x[-which.max(x)])))
cor.diff.col <- apply(cor.m, 2, function(x) x - max(x[-which.max(x)]))
cor.diff.rowl <- melt(cor.diff.row)
cor.diff.coll <- melt(cor.diff.col)
cor.diff <- apply(cbind(cor.diff.rowl$value, cor.diff.coll$value), 1, min)
cor.diffm <- matrix(cor.diff, nrow(cor.m), ncol(cor.m))
cor.m2l <- melt(cor.m2)
cor.m2l$specificity <- ifelse(cor.diff < 0, 0, cor.diff) #- min(cor.diffl$value)
cor.m2l$cor <- cor.ml$value

cor.m2l$homology_type <- as.factor(cor.m2l$value)
homol.df <- data.frame(orig_lev = c("0", "1", "2", "3", "4"), 
                       new_lev = c("None", paste(names(paths)[1], "best match"), 
                                   paste(names(paths)[2], "best match"), 
                                   "Reciprocal best match", "One-to-one"),
                       lev_color = c("#FFFFFF00", "light blue", "pink", "darkorchid1", "darkorchid4"))
levels(cor.m2l$homology_type) <- homol.df$new_lev[match(levels(cor.m2l$homology_type), homol.df$orig_lev)]
homol.pal <- as.character(homol.df$lev_color[match(levels(cor.m2l$homology_type), homol.df$new_lev)])

g2 <- ggplot(cor.m2l, aes(x = Var2, y = Var1, size = specificity, color = homology_type)) +
  geom_point() +

For unique best matching clusters, compare cluster proportions

cl.match <- cbind(rownames(cor.m2)[apply(cor.m2, 2, which.max)], 
                  colnames(cor.m2))
good.match <- which(apply(cor.m2, 2, max) >= 3 & apply(cor.diffm, 2, max) > 0.0)
cl.to.plot <- cl.match[good.match, ]
# cl.to.plot <- cl.to.plot[order(cl.to.plot[, 2]), ]

if (nrow(cl.to.plot) > 0) {
  
  # Cluster sizes
  cl.prop <- list()
  for (i in 1:2) { 
    cl.cnt1 <- as.matrix(table(anno[[i]]$cluster_label))
    cl.cnt.subset <- cl.cnt1[rownames(cl.cnt1) %in% unlist(cl.to.plot), ]
    cl.prop[[i]] <- cl.cnt.subset / sum(cl.cnt.subset)
  }
  
  cl1.prop.subset <- cl.prop[[1]][cl.to.plot[, 1]]
  cl2.prop.subset <- cl.prop[[2]][cl.to.plot[, 2]]
  
  cor1 <- round(cor(cl2.prop.subset, cl1.prop.subset), 2)
  plot(cl2.prop.subset, cl1.prop.subset, 
       type = "p", xlim = c(0, max(cl.prop[[2]])), ylim = c(0, max(cl.prop[[1]])), 
       xlab = names(paths)[2], ylab = names(paths)[1], 
       main = paste0("Cluster proportion (r = ", cor1, ")"))
  abline(0, 1)
  text(cl2.prop.subset, cl1.prop.subset, labels = cl.to.plot[, 2], cex = 0.5, pos = 1)
}

For unique best matching clusters, plot expression of marker genes.

Label genes that are cell type specific in both data sets.

if (nrow(cl.to.plot) > 0) {
  shared.marker.genes <- list()
  par(mfrow = c(ceiling(sqrt(nrow(cl.to.plot))), ceiling(sqrt(nrow(cl.to.plot)))))
  for (i in 1:nrow(cl.to.plot)) {
    cl1 <- cl.to.plot[i, 1]
    cl2 <- cl.to.plot[i, 2]
    
    cor1 <- cov.wt(cbind(prop.subset[[1]][, cl1], prop.subset[[2]][, cl2]), wt = cor.wt,
                   center = TRUE, cor = TRUE)$cor[1, 2]  # Weighted cor
    label.genes <- prop.subset[[1]][, cl1] > 0.5 & prop.subset[[2]][, cl2] > 0.5 &
      (cnt.subset[[1]] == 1 | cnt.subset[[2]] == 1)
    # label.genes <- prop.subset[[1]][, cl1] > 0.5 & prop.subset[[2]][, cl2] < 0.1 |
    #   prop.subset[[1]][, cl1] < 0.1 & prop.subset[[2]][, cl2] > 0.5
    
    plot(jitter(prop.subset[[2]][, cl2]),
         jitter(prop.subset[[1]][, cl1]), 
         xlab = cl2, ylab = cl1, pch = 19, cex = 0.2, 
         xlim = c(0, 1), ylim = c(0, 1), main = paste("r =", signif(cor1, 2)))
    abline(0, 1, col = "grey")
    if (sum(label.genes) > 0) {
      text(jitter(prop.subset[[2]][label.genes, cl2]),
           jitter(prop.subset[[1]][label.genes, cl1]), 
           rownames(prop.subset[[1]])[label.genes], cex = 1)
      cl.pair.name <- paste(cl1, cl2)
      shared.marker.genes[[cl.pair.name]] <- rownames(prop.subset[[1]])[label.genes]
    }
  }
}

class.cnt1 <- t(apply(prop.subset[[1]], 1, function(x) {
  cnt1 <- tapply(x, anno.cl[[1]]$cluster_type_label, function(y) sum(y > 0.5))
  paste(names(cnt1)[cnt1 > 0], collapse = "_")
}))

class.cnt2 <- t(apply(prop.subset[[2]], 1, function(x) {
  cnt1 <- tapply(x, anno.cl[[2]]$category_label, function(y) sum(y > 0.8))
  paste(names(cnt1)[cnt1 > 0], collapse = "_")
}))

cnt.tab <- table(class.cnt1, class.cnt2)
pheatmap(log2(cnt.tab + 1), cluster_rows = FALSE, cluster_cols = FALSE)

# Plot single gene
cor.breaks <- seq(-1, 1, 0.01)

  prop.diffm <- matrix(prop.diff.scaled[gene1, ], nrow(cor.m), ncol(cor.m), 
                       dimnames = list(rownames(cor.m), colnames(cor.m)))
  pheatmap(prop.diffm, breaks = cor.breaks, color = div.pal, border_color = NA,
           main = gene1, fontsize_row = 5, fontsize_col = 5, 
           cluster_rows = FALSE, cluster_cols = FALSE)

# Summarize by broad classes
matrix.idx <- cbind(as.numeric(row(cor.m2)), as.numeric(col(cor.m2)))
inh1 <- matrix.idx[, 1] %in% which(anno.cl[[1]]$cluster_type_label == "inh")
inh2 <- matrix.idx[, 2] %in% which(anno.cl[[2]]$category_label == "GABAergic")
exc1 <- matrix.idx[, 1] %in% which(anno.cl[[1]]$cluster_type_label == "exc")
exc2 <- matrix.idx[, 2] %in% which(anno.cl[[2]]$category_label == "Glutamatergic")
glia1 <- matrix.idx[, 1] %in% which(anno.cl[[1]]$cluster_type_label == "glia")
glia2 <- matrix.idx[, 2] %in% which(anno.cl[[2]]$category_label == "Non-Neuronal")

prop.diff.byclass <- t(apply(prop.diff.scaled, 1, function(x) {
  inh.prop <- x[inh1 & inh2]
  exc.prop <- x[exc1 & exc2]
  glia.prop <- x[glia1 & glia2]
  prop.diff.thresh <- 0.5
  prop.pattern <- c(m.inh.up = any(inh.prop < -prop.diff.thresh) * 1, 
                    m.exc.up = any(exc.prop < -prop.diff.thresh) * 1,
                    m.glia.up = any(glia.prop < -prop.diff.thresh) * 1,
                    h.inh.up = any(inh.prop > prop.diff.thresh) * 1,
                    h.exc.up = any(exc.prop > prop.diff.thresh) * 1,
                    h.glia.up = any(glia.prop > prop.diff.thresh) * 1)
}))
# prop.diff.byclass <- prop.diff.byclass[which(apply(prop.diff.byclass, 1, max) > 0), ]
order1 <- order(apply(prop.diff.byclass, 1, function(x) sum(x * c(1,2,4,8,16,32))))
# pdf(file="../tmp/plot5.pdf", width = 30, height = 30)
pheatmap(prop.diff.byclass[order1, ], cluster_rows = FALSE, cluster_cols = FALSE,
         fontsize_row = 2)
